list.item:
Conscious of the responsibility which rests upon them for restoring
                            through the victory of the United Nations the rule of justice throughout
                            the world;

Call upon all neutral countries to refuse asylum to persons fleeing
                            from the consequences of their crimes, whose object, or probable object,
                            in seeking asylum is to avoid falling into the hands of the United
                            Nations or who seek it in consequence or in anticipation of defeat of
                            their country or of its occupation by the Forces of the United
                            Nations;
